Benedictum --- Numerus Sacer (Sacred Number)

The machine asks you for a number between 0 and 255.
It will double it and return it, blessed.

If you give it 42, it returns 84.
If you give it 100, it returns 200.
What overflows, the tape accepts without complaint.

Cell layout:
  C0 = the offering (read from stdin, then zeroed as we copy)
  C1 = first copy  (restored to C0)
  C2 = second copy (added to C0)

Read the offering.

numerus

Copy C0 into both C1 and C2 simultaneously.

ora
    male
    dex bene
    dex bene
    sin sin
amen

C0 is now 0. C1 = N. C2 = N.

Restore C0 from C1.

dex
ora
    male
    sin bene
    dex
amen
sin

C0 = N. Now add C2 to C0 for the doubling.

dex dex
ora
    male
    sin sin bene
    dex dex
amen
sin sin

Speak the doubled number into the light.

lux nox
